JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 79
IS  - 1
SP  - 375
EP  - 387
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - An individual displays various preference orderings in different payoff-irrelevant circumstances. It is assumed that the variation in the observed preference orderings is the outcome of some cognitive process that distorts the underlying preferences of the individual. We introduce a framework for eliciting the individual's underlying preferences in such cases and then demonstrate it for two cognitive processes—satisficing and small assessment errors.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
